        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued August 23 at 10:49PM EDT until August 26 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Waves 2 to 5 feet tonight and Sunday, but building to 3
to 6 feet Sunday night and Monday before receding to 2 to 4 feet
Monday night and Tuesday. Waves Life-threatening waves and
currents and, therefore, dangerous swimming conditions expected.
Piers will be heavily swamped by waves.

* WHERE...In Indiana, Northern La Porte county. In Michigan,
Northern Berrien and Southern Berrien counties.

* WHEN...Through Tuesday evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not venture out on piers.</instruction>
